For more on that, you can watch my episode

106
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:46,290
“5 Countries That Have Fallen into China's
Debt Trap”

107
00:04:46,290 --> 00:04:48,620
for all the sordid details of how China

108
00:04:48,620 --> 00:04:52,540
leverages debt to get what it wants.

109
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:56,760
Wow, I forgot there was a time

110
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:59,090
when I didn’t have a beard.

111
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,890
Anyway, why would the Chinese regime

112
00:05:00,890 --> 00:05:02,610
care about Cameroon?

113
00:05:02,610 --> 00:05:05,450
Well, for one: mineral resources.

114
00:05:05,450 --> 00:05:08,180
Like bauxite, iron ore, and gold.

115
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:10,640
And don’t worry, Chinese gold mining operations

116
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:14,980
there are totally legit and have no problems
whatsoever.

117
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:18,440
Ok, a few minor problems.

118
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:22,620
But look, there’s another reason China cares
about Cameroon.

119
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:24,860
Let’s go back to that map.

120
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:27,070
Cameroon sits along the Gulf of Guinea.

121
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:29,070
And that’s a good place to be when doing
trade

122
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:32,700
with a dozen other countries, like Nigeria.

123
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,150
So it should come as no surprise that China

124
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:38,140
has invested 1.2 billion dollars

125
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:40,610
to convert a fishing town called Kribi

126
00:05:40,610 --> 00:05:44,490
into the region’s biggest deep-water port.

127
00:05:44,490 --> 00:05:48,740
“Made up of four main parts,

128
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:51,800
a deep water port with roughly 20 wharfs,

129
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:56,270
a zone for industrial and logistics activity,

130
00:05:56,270 --> 00:05:59,120
a multi-modal transport corridor,

131
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,220
a new city.”

132
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:03,020
And Cameroon’s Kribi port

133
00:06:03,020 --> 00:06:05,600
is connected to a pipeline project

134
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:08,190
to bring in oil from land-locked Chad.

135
00:06:08,190 --> 00:06:14,220
There’s also a 436 million dollar highway
China is funding there.

136
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:18,840
It ties the port with Cameroon's resource-rich
inland area.

137
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,370
And there are also plans to build a railroad

138
00:06:21,370 --> 00:06:24,750
directly to a deposit of iron ore.

139
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:29,210
And those iron mines will definitely not have
problems.

140
00:06:29,210 --> 00:06:30,780
So far it doesn’t look like Cameroon

141
00:06:30,780 --> 00:06:35,330
has had to directly give up any of its infrastructure
or resources

142
00:06:35,330 --> 00:06:38,310
for the 78 million dollars in debt forgiveness.

143
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:42,340
But the Chinese Communist Party’s overall
actions in Cameroon

144
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:46,770
are clearly the same strategy it has used
around the world:

145
00:06:46,770 --> 00:06:48,840
Make generous loans,

146
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,390
get countries in debt,

147
00:06:50,390 --> 00:06:54,050
and forgive the debt in exchange for small
things—

148
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:58,020
like all of their resources, or strategic
infrastructure.

149
00:06:58,020 --> 00:07:00,110
Win-win mutual cooperation.

150
00:07:00,110 --> 00:07:02,620
Which means that China-Cameroon relations

151
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:05,030
should be something to keep an eye on.

